They were really aiming, however, at the shadows of the enemy, cast in front of them by the moon shining behind (a tergo), and hence their missiles fell short of the real ob- ject. It was thus that the rising of the moon not only revealed the armies, but deceived them. A charming account of this optical illu- sion in the midst of this terrible fight by night.
